{"word":"H7651 - שֶׁבַע - shebaʻ - sheh'-bah - Seven","slug":"H7651","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שֶׁבַע</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>shebaʻ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>sheh'-bah"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Seven"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D1;&#x05E2;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D1;&#x05E2; - sheba&#x201B;  shib&#x201B;a&#x0302;h</b> - <i>sheh'-bah, shib-aw'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H7650\">H7650</a>; a primitive cardinal number; <i>seven</i> (as the sacred <i>full</i> one); also (adverbially) <i>seven times</i>; by implication a <i>week</i>; by extension an <i>indefinite</i> number: -  (+ by) seven ([-fold], -s, [-teen, -teenth], -th, times). Compare <a href=\"#/H7658\">H7658</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7620\">H7620</a>, <a href=\"#/H7621\">H7621</a>, <a href=\"#/H7637\">H7637</a>, <a href=\"#/H7650\">H7650</a>, <a href=\"#/H7652\">H7652</a>, <a href=\"#/H7656\">H7656</a>, <a href=\"#/H7657\">H7657</a>, <a href=\"#/H7658\">H7658</a>, <a href=\"#/H7659\">H7659</a>"}]}